  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT262-kilavi">uṭaṉpōkku nērnta tōḻi kiḻattikku uṭaṉpōkku uṇarttiyatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">The confidante, who had granted going away together,
          announcing to HER the going away together. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT262">
          <l> ūu ralareḻac cēri kalleṉa</l>
          <l> vāṉā talaikku maṟaṉi laṉṉai</l>
          <l> tāṉē yirukka taṉmaṉai yāṉē</l>
          <l> nelli tiṉṟa muḷḷeyiṟu tayaṅka</l>
          <l> vuṇalāyn ticiṉā lavaroṭu cēynāṭṭu</l>
          <l> viṇṭoṭa nivanta vilaṅkumalaik kavāaṟ</l>
          <l> karumpunaṭu pātti yaṉṉa</l>
          <l> peruṅkaḷiṟ ṟaṭivaḻi nilaiiya nīrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l rend="indent3">So that gossip arise in the village, so that the streets resound,</l>
          <l>let [my] dutiful <note place="foot">
              <term xml:lang="ta">aṟanil</term> : or "derelict in duty", cf. KT 244.6.</note>
            mother, who slaps [me] unendingly,</l>
          <l>be [alone] in her house.</l>
          <l rend="indent8">As for me,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">with [my] thorn teeth glittering after they have eaten Nelli [fruit],</l>
          <l>I have chosen to drink</l>
          <l rend="indent">the water which has lasted in the footprints <note place="foot">
              <term xml:lang="ta">aṭi-vaḻi</term> : is this a single footprint or is it a
            downtrodden path? And what does it suggest? The danger of a path also used by elephants?</note>
            of big elephant bulls,</l>
          <l rend="indent">[big] as [irrigation] troughs in the middle of sugarcane [fields], <note place="foot">How to understand the construction of this comparison? Does it refer to
            the size of the footprints?</note>
          </l>
          <l rend="indent4">on the slopes of transverse mountains that have come up</l>
          <l rend="indent7">to touch the sky, in a distant land with him.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
